<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section id="how" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">→ How it works</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Three steps. <span class="accent">Ninety days.</span> Zero infrastructure.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">No magnetic strips on the floor. No QR codes on the walls. DriveMod uses 3D LiDAR and onboard intelligence — so deployment fits your timeline, not your facility shutdown schedule.</p>

    <div class="steps-grid">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">01 — Assess</div>
        <div class="step-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><path d="m21 21-4.35-4.35"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="step-title">Workflow audit & ROI model</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Our solutions engineers walk your facility, audit current tugger routes, and build a customer-specific payback model. You see exactly which routes produce ROI before any capital commits.</div>
        <div class="step-meta">
          <span>Timeline</span>
          <strong>2 weeks</strong>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">02 — Retrofit</div>
        <div class="step-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="step-title">DriveMod retrofit on existing fleet</div>
        <div class="step-desc">We integrate DriveMod onto your Motrec MT-160 tuggers — the same vehicles your team already operates and maintains. No new hardware platform. No retraining the maintenance crew.</div>
        <div class="step-meta">
          <span>Timeline</span>
          <strong>4–6 weeks</strong>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">03 — Deploy</div>
        <div class="step-icon">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m12 19 7-7 3 3-7 7-3-3z"/><path d="m18 13-1.5-7.5L2 2l3.5 14.5L13 18l5-5z"/><path d="m2 2 7.586 7.586"/><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="step-title">Live ops with onboard FMS</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Vehicles ship with on-vehicle displays, cloud FMS, and tablet stations throughout your facility. Your team controls dispatch like elevator buttons. WMS integration included.</div>
        <div class="step-meta">
          <span>Timeline</span>
          <strong>2–4 weeks</strong>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE MATH -->
<section id="math" class="section math-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="math-grid">
      <div class="math-text">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">→ The math</div>
        <h2>Not automating costs <span style="color: var(--accent); font-style: italic;">4× more</span> than retrofitting.</h2>
        <p>A single tugger driver in a 24/7 facility costs roughly <strong>$165,000/year fully loaded</strong> across 3 shifts. Multiply by fleet size and the number gets uncomfortable fast.</p>
        <p>DriveMod retrofits don't replace your operators — they redeploy them. Your headcount moves to higher-judgment work (loading, picking, troubleshooting) while the tugger does what tuggers do best: <strong>repeat the same route, perfectly, forever, without complaint.</strong></p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 24px;">Source: Cyngn customer ROI analyses, 2024–2026.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="math-callouts">
        <div class="callout">
          <div class="callout-num">$165K</div>
          <div class="callout-label">Annual cost / tugger / 24-7 facility</div>
          <div class="callout-detail">Fully-loaded labor: 3 shifts × ~$55K/year per operator including benefits, overtime, and turnover replacement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="callout">
          <div class="callout-num">−64%</div>
          <div class="callout-label">Average labor cost reduction</div>
          <div class="callout-detail">Across deployed Cyngn customers, autonomous tugger routes reduced direct labor cost by an average of 64%.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="callout">
          <div class="callout-num">12,000<span style="font-size: 32px; color: var(--text-muted);"> lb</span></div>
          <div class="callout-label">Train capacity per tugger</div>
          <div class="callout-detail">Multi-cart tugger trains. Auto-unhitch. Indoor and outdoor. WMS-integrated mission orchestration.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

